com.yworks.yfiles.layout.hierarchic

Class TopologicalLayerer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.layout.hierarchic.TopologicalLayerer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILayerer

    public class TopologicalLayerer
extends Object
implements ILayerer
    This class implements the layering phase of the HierarchicLayout (i.e., assignment of the nodes to layers).

    It uses topological sorting to assign layers to the nodes.

      • assignNodeLayer

        public int assignNodeLayer(LayoutGraph graph,
                           INodeMap layerID,
                           EdgeList reversedEdges)
        This method assigns the nodes in the graph to layers.
        Postcondition:
        For all (v,w) in E: layer(v) < layer(w)
        Parameters:
        graph - the given graph
        layerID - the INodeMap that will be filled by the layout algorithm and returns the zero-based index of the layer to which each node belongs
        reversedEdges - an EdgeList containing the edges which had been reversed
        Returns:
        the number of layers
